<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,690,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[625,743,690,714]" name="Venezuela" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[757,811,691,714]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[826,911,690,714]" name="Bolivia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[925,1038,690,714]" name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, Guianas and northern and central 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,726,750]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, throughout humid forests of Amazonia and the northern part of the Atlantic Forest and the drier biomes of Cerrado and Caatinga (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner" box="[409,571,762,786]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Gardner, A. L. (2007) American marsupials. In: Gardner, A. L. (Ed), Mammals of South America, Volume 1. The University of Chicago Press, Chicago, pp. 1 - 126." type="book" year="2007">
Gardner 
<number box="[510,571,762,786]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,222,932]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,386,798,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Natural history.</emphasis>
Twenty-two individuals of 
<taxonomicName box="[696,854,798,823]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Micoureus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="demerarae">
<emphasis box="[696,854,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. demerarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, eleven of each sex, were captured on the ground (n = 
<number box="[175,203,834,858]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="18.0">18</number>
) and in the understory (n = 
<number box="[523,538,834,858]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
) of flooded and upland forest. Six reproductively active females were captured from 
<date box="[212,483,870,894]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2007-06" valueMax="2007-11-31" valueMin="2007-06-00">
June to November 
<number box="[424,483,870,894]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</date>
, three lactating and one with six pouch young and two with eleven pouch young.
</paragraph>
